e="preserve">Munah Evangeline Pelham-Youngblood (22 September 19838 July 2020) was a Liberian politician. She was elected twice to the Liberian House of Representatives. She was the youngest person ever elected to the Liberian parliament. She was a member of Congress for Democratic Change. She worked for President George Weah.
Pelham-Youngblood died in Accra, Ghana, on 8 July 2020 at the age of 36.
